deprecation.message: Only versions 5.x of MathParser.org-mXparser are going to be maintained. From now on all the previous versions are legacy. API of versions 5.x are fully backward compatible with all 4.x. Technical migrating to 5.x should be hassle free.

description: mXparser is a super easy, rich, fast and highly flexible math expression parser library (parser and evaluator of mathematical expressions / formulas provided as plain text / string). Software delivers easy to use API for JAVA, Android and C# .NET/MONO (Common Language Specification compliant: F#, Visual Basic, C++/CLI). *** If you finnd the software useful donation is something you might consider: http://mathparser.org/donate/ ***
releaseNotes: v.4.1.0 Aeries - Major update: Various numeral systems + Working with digits (number of digits, digit at position), Leading zeros, Prime factorization, Not-a-Number support, Variadic or + and + xor, Other nice functions (argmin, argmax, root, mode, median, coalesce), Percentage '%' as operator, Alternative syntax for derivative, Built-in tokens manipulation, Interacting with expression tokens.
summary: mXparser is a super easy, rich, fast and highly flexible math expression parser library (parser and evaluator of mathematical expressions / formulas provided as plain text / string). Software delivers easy to use API for JAVA, Android and C# .NET/MONO (Common Language Specification compliant: F#, Visual Basic, C++/CLI). Expression parser comes with extensive documentation, easy to follow tutorial, "Hello World!" projects for different languages explained with many screenshots, and finally - last, but not least - performance test summary. Formula evaluator is distributed under "Simplified BSD license", which means software is completely free.
